Docker Commands
--------------------------
    docker --version      : to check the version of Docker
    docker images        : to check the docker images present in my system

tags – typically used for versioning

docker image by name hello-world typically used for test whether docker is working or not.


    docker images                   : listing images

    docker rmi <image name/id>      : removing images

    docker pull <image name>   : to pull images for dockerHub

    docker pull <image name>:tagname   : to pull images with tag name

    docker run <image name>  : start container(to run image) and run pgms

    docker ps -a                    : List all containers

    docker ps                       : list running containers

    docker rm <containerid/name>    : removing stopped containers

    docker container prune          : remove all stopped containers

    docker stop <containerid/name>  : stop a running container

    docker network create <networkname>  : create own bridge network

    docker network ls                  : list networks

    docker logs <containerid/name>      : see the container logs
    docker logs -f <containerid/name>   : follow the new logs


    docker exec -it 17b6d663cf82 bash   : get inside the container in a terminal

  docker info : will give info about docker,root directory……
